  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Send 25 Orphans to School-Donate Pigs in Cameroon</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">We believe something as simple as a pig can radically change the lives of village orphans living in severe poverty. By donating two piglets to each orphan&apos;s caretaker the household can sell the pigs each year to pay school fees, with the seed money re-invested into the project to help more orphans. BERUDA&apos;s Orphan Education Through Pig-Rearing Project provides a sustainable means for 25 orphans to pay their school fees in rural Cameroon. A piglet given today, can grow into an education tomorrow.</narrative>
  </description>
